#   BE — dispatcher CLI tickets

`be`'s front-end: verb/projector dispatch, bareword routing, and the error/UX surface a user actually sees. One topic dir, [Plan]-shaped tickets cleared by the [Issues] fix-and-land loop.

##  Active tickets

 -  [BE-001] — red leaks into non-conflict code render and ulog status rows; restrict red to the `conf`/`modl` conflict statuses ([DIS-018]), default everything else.
 -  [BE-002] — cryptic errors for mistyped verbs/projectors (`be difff` → `bro: cannot open difff: FILENONE`, exit 0); add a `DOGSuggestCommand` "did you mean" suggester + own the diagnostic in `be` with a non-zero exit.
 -  [BE-003] — every dog must print **name + verb + URI + error code** on an error exit (one uniform line, single-sourced) — today error exits are contextless (`Error: SNIFFFAIL`, `bro: cannot open …: FILENONE`); general form of BE-002.

